WEBVTT

00:00.701 --> 00:03.736
Lovers of liberty,
are we to believe this man

00:03.738 --> 00:05.270
<i> Is capable</i>
<i> of guiding our nation</i>

00:05.272 --> 00:06.572
<i> With prudence and common sense</i>

00:06.574 --> 00:09.274
<i> With that seductress</i>
<i> olivia pope</i>

00:09.276 --> 00:12.778
<i> Distracting him</i>
<i> with a body made for --</i>

00:12.780 --> 00:15.581
<i> Dennis, will you show us</i>
<i> the photographs again?</i>

00:15.583 --> 00:19.218
<i> We've been sold a bushel</i>
<i>of lies, a barrel of snake oil.</i>

00:19.220 --> 00:21.020
[ tv turns off,
remote clatters ]

00:21.022 --> 00:22.421
Liv.

00:25.192 --> 00:28.494
Liv, everything's
gonna be okay.

00:28.496 --> 00:31.430
I have to go downstairs now,
before abby and liz get up here,

00:31.432 --> 00:33.499
But i'll be right back
as soon as i can.

00:33.501 --> 00:35.234
Everything's gonna be okay.

00:41.509 --> 00:43.275
[ door opens ]

00:43.277 --> 00:45.544
[ door closes ]

00:45.546 --> 00:46.979
How the hell
did this happen?

00:46.980 --> 00:48.413
Head of the uniformed
secret service confirms

00:48.416 --> 00:50.149
There were no
external security breaches.

00:50.151 --> 00:51.601
But that's really not
the issue, sir.

00:51.602 --> 00:53.052
So, you're telling me
this leak was internal?

00:53.054 --> 00:54.653
Sir, the leak
is really not the issue.

00:54.655 --> 00:56.522
I want the head of the uniformed
secret service in here now.

00:56.524 --> 00:58.424
Can't. I just fired him.
I'm bringing my guy in
from the nsa.

00:58.426 --> 01:00.292
Not the issue.
No, get rosen
to investigate the leak.

01:00.294 --> 01:02.127
Sir, this is
a surveillance issue.

01:02.129 --> 01:03.695
Rosen's loyal to liv.
He's on the inside.

01:03.697 --> 01:06.131
He'll want to make
this happen right.
Not the issue.

01:06.133 --> 01:07.833
Sir, those photos
are everywhere.

01:07.835 --> 01:09.735
I've got a roomful of press
getting rowdier by the minute.

01:09.737 --> 01:11.470
There's blood in the water.

01:11.471 --> 01:13.204
We're gonna need a game plan.
We're gonna need a statement.

01:13.207 --> 01:15.240
We're gonna need...
A bigger boat.

01:15.242 --> 01:16.742
She's right.

01:16.744 --> 01:19.278
The press needs to hear from
the white house -- from you.

01:19.280 --> 01:21.146
Sir?

01:21.148 --> 01:22.247
I'm going back
to the residence.

01:22.249 --> 01:24.116
Because?
Because olivia is there.

01:24.118 --> 01:26.185
I can't make a statement
without olivia.

01:26.187 --> 01:28.320
Mr. President,
i don't think that's a good --
if a statement is being made,

01:28.322 --> 01:31.190
Olivia and i
are making it together.

01:34.261 --> 01:36.695
So, what --
history's being made tonight?

01:36.697 --> 01:39.231
For the first time ever,
the president and his mistress

01:39.233 --> 01:40.732
Address the nation.

01:40.734 --> 01:43.135
Why are you so calm?

01:43.137 --> 01:44.803
Do you really think she's gonna
get in front of the camera

01:44.805 --> 01:46.338
And admit that they're having
an affair?

01:46.340 --> 01:48.140
It's liv.
She's the best in the business.

01:48.142 --> 01:49.641
The president's about
to get poped.

01:52.246 --> 01:53.645
Liv?

01:53.647 --> 01:56.515
[ cellphone rings ]

01:56.517 --> 01:58.150
What's going on?

01:58.152 --> 02:00.052
I had to leave
while i still could.

02:00.054 --> 02:01.353
-Liv --
-don't call me again.

02:01.355 --> 02:02.855
Wait for me.
I will call you.

02:02.857 --> 02:04.556
Liv, where the hell
are you?

02:04.558 --> 02:06.291
Well,
what a ludicrous question.

02:06.293 --> 02:09.428
We know exactly where she is.

02:09.430 --> 02:12.364
She may run from the watchful
eyes of justice.

02:12.366 --> 02:15.300
She may run from the good people
of this nation.

02:15.302 --> 02:17.503
But i can assure you,
dear lovers of liberty,

02:17.505 --> 02:19.838
She will not be able to hide.

02:24.912 --> 02:27.212
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

02:30.885 --> 02:33.485
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

02:33.487 --> 02:34.820
Liv, oh, my god.
Are you okay?

02:34.822 --> 02:36.372
-I'm fine.
-Were you followed?

02:36.373 --> 02:37.923
Quinn, close the door
and put the gun away.

02:37.925 --> 02:39.358
They're reporters,
not assassins.

02:39.360 --> 02:40.692
Here, sit down.
I'm sorry.

02:40.694 --> 02:42.294
This place is a mess.
What do you need?

02:42.296 --> 02:43.862
Oh, can i get you something
to drink?

02:43.864 --> 02:47.699
I have water, i have tea,
i have wine.

02:50.938 --> 02:53.539
Liv, tell me how to help.
What can i do?

02:53.541 --> 02:55.407
What do we have?

02:55.409 --> 02:57.743
-What do we --
-cases, work -- new cases.

02:57.745 --> 02:59.411
What do we have?
-What?

02:59.413 --> 03:01.380
I need to work.

03:01.381 --> 03:03.348
Calls to the first lady's
office have not been returned,

03:03.350 --> 03:04.917
And still no statement
from the white house.

03:04.919 --> 03:06.618
There's been a great deal
of speculation

03:06.620 --> 03:08.820
Heading into this morning's
white house press briefing,

03:08.822 --> 03:11.323
Many wondering if
press secretary abigail whelan

03:11.325 --> 03:13.492
Will address the question
on everyone's mind.

03:13.494 --> 03:16.628
[ indistinct shouting ]
hey, people, hey!

03:16.630 --> 03:18.330
I am not going to answer
your questions

03:18.332 --> 03:19.598
If you're shouting all at once.

03:19.600 --> 03:21.333
You're not gonna answer
our questions either way.

03:21.335 --> 03:22.901
When can we expect a statement
from the president himself?

03:22.903 --> 03:25.637
Whenever the president himself
decides to make a statement.

03:25.639 --> 03:26.638
See what i mean?
[ indistinct shouting ]

03:30.411 --> 03:31.476
Mellie.

03:31.478 --> 03:34.947
Yes, fitz?

03:34.949 --> 03:37.249
Why are you here?

03:40.487 --> 03:43.488
Well, for starters, i am here
so that you can apologize to me.

03:43.490 --> 03:46.491
What?
So you can apologize to me,

03:46.493 --> 03:50.796
Which is very generous of me,
i think -- me coming to<i> you.</i>

03:50.798 --> 03:52.664
But given the little problem
you have going on,

03:52.666 --> 03:55.767
It seemed better for me
to come here for the optics.

03:55.769 --> 03:57.803
The optics, right.

03:57.805 --> 03:59.605
What in the hell
are you talking about?

03:59.607 --> 04:01.506
Come on.

04:01.508 --> 04:03.575
Do we really have to do it
this way?

04:03.577 --> 04:04.743
Do we have to pretend?

04:04.745 --> 04:06.511
Can't you just...

04:06.513 --> 04:09.414
All the pride and the ego
and just admit it?

04:09.416 --> 04:11.316
Admit what?

04:11.318 --> 04:14.319
[ sighs, scoffs ]

04:14.321 --> 04:16.488
Okay, fine.

04:16.490 --> 04:18.357
You want to play?

04:18.359 --> 04:21.393
Let's play.

04:21.395 --> 04:24.363
You placed olivia
in a dangerous position.

04:24.365 --> 04:26.398
You outed her.
[ scoffs ]

04:26.400 --> 04:28.500
You thought by throwing me
out of the white house

04:28.502 --> 04:30.769
And moving her in, you'd be
making this grand gesture.

04:30.771 --> 04:32.838
Finally, she wouldn't be
just a mistress anymore.

04:32.840 --> 04:34.806
But the minute she stepped
through these doors,

04:34.808 --> 04:37.309
The<i> minute</i>
she moved in here,

04:37.311 --> 04:38.644
She became what we all become
when we live here,

04:38.646 --> 04:40.012
And what is that?

04:40.014 --> 04:41.980
Yes.

04:41.982 --> 04:45.817
A statue, inhuman,

04:45.819 --> 04:49.721
Viewed from every angle,
discussed, exposed.

04:49.723 --> 04:52.291
She's not just
a mistress now.

04:52.293 --> 04:54.526
She's america's mistress.

04:54.528 --> 04:57.496
History will preserve her
as such.

04:57.498 --> 04:59.698
Oh, honey.

04:59.700 --> 05:01.900
You made
a horrible miscalculation,

05:01.902 --> 05:04.303
An error in judgment.

05:04.305 --> 05:07.339
You didn't realize,
which is why i am here --

05:07.341 --> 05:09.875
So that you can apologize,
i can accept,

05:09.877 --> 05:11.576
And then i'll take care
of everything.

05:11.578 --> 05:12.844
It's gonna be okay.
Don't worry.

05:12.846 --> 05:14.313
Wait.

05:14.315 --> 05:15.614
What?

05:15.616 --> 05:17.983
I will deny sally's story,
say you and olivia

05:17.985 --> 05:19.518
Were nothing more
than a trashy rumor,

05:19.520 --> 05:20.986
Remind everyone
what close friends we are.

05:20.988 --> 05:22.721
"of course she was here
late at night.

05:22.723 --> 05:24.423
So was her boyfriend."

05:24.425 --> 05:26.325
We'll pick someone,
one of your friends,

05:26.327 --> 05:27.859
Someone of similar height
and build.

05:27.861 --> 05:30.662
As for you and me...
We're fine.

05:30.664 --> 05:32.064
We couldn't be better.

05:32.066 --> 05:33.565
And the apology?

05:33.567 --> 05:35.667
[ sighs ]

05:35.669 --> 05:37.602
You said i need
to apologize.

05:37.604 --> 05:39.771
For those divorce papers.

05:39.773 --> 05:42.040
That was mean.

05:42.042 --> 05:43.608
That hurt my feelings.

05:43.610 --> 05:45.610
[ clears throat ]

05:45.612 --> 05:47.913
You can admit
that was mean, right?

05:47.915 --> 05:50.615
[ smacks lips ]

05:50.617 --> 05:52.017
I am not going to bring

05:52.019 --> 05:54.786
Our children
to visit you in jail.

05:54.788 --> 05:56.655
Excuse me?

05:56.657 --> 05:58.757
When you gave those photos
to sally langston,

05:58.759 --> 06:00.759
You didn't just leak
this olivia business.

06:00.761 --> 06:02.361
You also broke the law.

06:02.363 --> 06:03.795
Wait a minute,
you think i did this?

06:03.797 --> 06:05.864
It was smart --
risky, but smart.
[ exhales sharply ]

06:05.866 --> 06:07.616
You don't want a divorce.

06:07.617 --> 06:09.367
You need some way
to worm your way back in here,

06:09.370 --> 06:11.903
So you leak a few pictures,
humiliate her,

06:11.905 --> 06:13.638
Play on my sense
of guilt,

06:13.640 --> 06:15.040
Then ride back in here
on your white broomstick to --

06:15.042 --> 06:18.443
Fitzgerald,
think about it.

06:18.445 --> 06:21.513
Those pictures made people feel
sorry for first lady grant,

06:21.515 --> 06:25.517
But they make
senator grant look weak

06:25.519 --> 06:28.520
And frigid and sexless
and like she can't keep a man.

06:28.522 --> 06:30.022
And we both know america

06:30.023 --> 06:31.523
Will never elect a woman
who can't get laid.

06:31.525 --> 06:33.792
Everything is always about
your presidential run.

06:33.794 --> 06:35.894
[ sighs ]

06:35.896 --> 06:39.831
That's why you want to move
back in and forget the divorce.

06:39.833 --> 06:42.567
We are a team.

06:42.569 --> 06:44.569
I need you.

06:44.571 --> 06:46.405
You need me.

06:46.407 --> 06:47.806
[ sighs ]

06:47.808 --> 06:50.542
And i am on board.

06:50.544 --> 06:53.845
I am ready, willing, and able
to put this whole thing to bed.

06:53.847 --> 06:56.114
All you have to do...

06:56.116 --> 06:58.116
[ sighs ]

06:58.118 --> 07:01.586
...Is just say
the magic words.

07:08.695 --> 07:11.563
Get...Out.

07:14.802 --> 07:16.902
[ scoffs ]

07:20.707 --> 07:23.141
[ breathes deeply ]

07:26.513 --> 07:28.113
[ door opens, slams ]

07:31.685 --> 07:33.068
We wait for olivia.

07:33.069 --> 07:34.452
I'd just like to be able
to have a strategy, sir.

07:34.455 --> 07:36.555
If we could --
<i> you</i> could consider

07:36.557 --> 07:37.923
Making a statement
without olivia --

07:37.925 --> 07:39.624
You keep repeating yourself,

07:39.626 --> 07:41.092
Like you think i don't hear
or i don't understand

07:41.094 --> 07:42.928
Or maybe you think
i'm gonna change my mind.

07:42.930 --> 07:44.763
Let's clear it up.

07:44.765 --> 07:46.498
I hear.
I understand.

07:46.500 --> 07:48.600
My mind will not change.

07:48.602 --> 07:50.569
Next subject.

07:50.571 --> 07:53.138
Next subject.
Well, abby?

07:53.140 --> 07:55.173
Sir, i noticed
that the first lady

07:55.175 --> 07:57.242
Paid a visit
to the oval earlier today.

07:57.244 --> 07:59.945
Is she
perhaps willing to...

08:01.648 --> 08:03.248
[ knock on door ]

08:03.250 --> 08:04.783
David's here!

08:04.785 --> 08:06.151
Hi.

08:06.153 --> 08:08.587
Mr. President,
i've opened the investigation

08:08.589 --> 08:09.688
Into the security breach,

08:09.690 --> 08:11.523
And your office
sent this list over.

08:11.525 --> 08:14.826
I -- the people on this list --
well, the name at the top --

08:14.828 --> 08:16.261
Do you want
to investigate her, sir?

08:16.263 --> 08:20.999
This whole situation is a load
of malarkey and doo-doo!

08:21.001 --> 08:23.635
As if you would ever have
an affair with olivia.

08:23.637 --> 08:27.272
My casey could make fake photos
like that in 15 minutes.

08:27.274 --> 08:29.875
I mean, obviously she wouldn't,
but she could.

08:29.877 --> 08:31.643
She's very good
with computers.

08:31.645 --> 08:33.712
I know mellie
leaked the photos.

08:33.714 --> 08:35.847
You just need to get proof.
-Yes, sir.

08:35.849 --> 08:37.883
Wait, so,
the photos are...

08:40.954 --> 08:42.888
Oh.

08:42.890 --> 08:47.092
Oh, i see.
Well...

08:47.094 --> 08:49.561
Oh.

08:49.563 --> 08:50.796
[ abby clears throat ]

08:50.797 --> 08:52.030
Could i at least
push the press briefing?

08:52.032 --> 08:53.665
Since we're not saying
anything

08:53.666 --> 08:55.299
And you're not changing
your mind, it would help --

08:55.302 --> 08:57.836
Pushing the briefing makes it
look like i'm ashamed or hiding.

08:57.838 --> 08:59.704
I'm not ashamed.
I'm not hiding.

08:59.706 --> 09:01.640
I'm waiting for olivia.

09:01.642 --> 09:03.542
Efforts to contact the woman
at the center

09:03.544 --> 09:05.977
Of this controversy --
d.C. Fixer olivia pope --

09:05.979 --> 09:08.046
Have so far been fruitless.

09:08.048 --> 09:09.948
You look like an idiot
out there.

09:09.950 --> 09:11.249
He needs
to say something.

09:11.251 --> 09:13.051
You need
to<i> make</i> him say something.

09:13.053 --> 09:14.953
I can't make the president
speak to the press.

09:14.955 --> 09:17.255
He is not a puppet.
He does not have strings.
He does.

09:17.257 --> 09:19.090
He does have strings,
but that -- that olivia

09:19.092 --> 09:21.092
Is in the wind, and she took
the strings with her.

09:21.094 --> 09:23.295
You didn't want him telling
the world about their affair.

09:23.297 --> 09:24.930
I told you
she would handle it.

09:24.932 --> 09:27.065
She handled it wrong.
I want the puppet to dance.

09:27.067 --> 09:29.267
Dan: Dan danzig coming to you
live in front of the building

09:29.269 --> 09:31.202
Where ms. Pope runs her
very own crisis-management firm.

09:31.204 --> 09:32.804
Still no sighting of pope
herself,

09:32.806 --> 09:34.272
But new details coming
to light this hour.

09:34.274 --> 09:36.875
The alleged presidential
mistress, sources tell us,

09:36.877 --> 09:38.977
Is a former swimming champion.

09:38.979 --> 09:40.278
Jake:
It's insane out there.

09:40.280 --> 09:42.013
The press has got
this building surrounded.

09:42.015 --> 09:43.748
[ sighs ]
jake, hey.

09:49.022 --> 09:50.922
What are you doing here?
Lay off, perkins.
He's here to help.

09:50.924 --> 09:52.257
Help?

09:52.259 --> 09:54.225
Well, if i need someone
to helpfully murder

09:54.227 --> 09:56.628
Busloads of innocent americans
and chop their heads off

09:56.630 --> 09:57.929
For fun,
i'll give huck a call.

09:57.931 --> 09:59.965
Otherwise, no, thanks.
I'm good.

09:59.967 --> 10:01.933
I'm fixed.
Jake fixed me.

10:01.935 --> 10:03.368
I'm okay now.
-Yeah, fixed?

10:03.370 --> 10:06.104
There aren't enough meds
in the world to fix --

10:06.106 --> 10:08.106
I'm here with him.
He's fine.

10:08.108 --> 10:09.808
Oh, you're like
his slaughter sponsor?

10:09.810 --> 10:11.176
Yeah, that's totally fine.
My bad.

10:11.178 --> 10:12.277
Can we put aside
the name-calling

10:12.278 --> 10:13.377
And the blood-feuding
and just get to work?

10:19.219 --> 10:20.619
Fine.

10:20.621 --> 10:22.287
Okay, now,
where is olivia?

10:22.289 --> 10:23.688
She's not here.
We took a case.

10:23.690 --> 10:25.390
Quinn, you what?

10:25.392 --> 10:27.225
We took a case.

10:27.226 --> 10:29.059
Walter was older than me,
and i know most people think,

10:29.062 --> 10:30.829
"wealthy older man,
younger woman."

10:30.831 --> 10:32.764
But, honestly,
i would have been happy

10:32.766 --> 10:34.232
If he'd been
a bus driver.

10:34.234 --> 10:37.736
I still can't -- that a son
could kill his own father.

10:37.738 --> 10:39.738
Gavin price, 35,

10:39.740 --> 10:42.307
Better known by his
uva frat brothers as "g-preezy."

10:42.309 --> 10:45.410
Mr. Preezy was indicted on
murder charges a few weeks ago.

10:45.412 --> 10:47.946
Murder of who?
Mega-developer
and real-estate tycoon

10:47.948 --> 10:49.714
Walter price, gavin's dad.

10:49.716 --> 10:51.783
You got an alibi, huck?

10:51.785 --> 10:53.385
[ stephanie sighs ]

10:53.386 --> 10:54.986
I'm sure gavin thought
it would look like an accident.

10:54.988 --> 10:56.955
I found them both
at the bottom of the stairs,

10:56.957 --> 10:58.790
Gavin covered
in walter's blood.

10:58.792 --> 11:00.992
Blunt-force trauma
to the head -- nasty fall.

11:00.994 --> 11:03.228
What about motive?
Doesn't every kid
want to kill their dad

11:03.230 --> 11:05.063
When he trades in
their biological mother

11:05.065 --> 11:07.265
For a younger,
more goal-oriented model?

11:07.267 --> 11:08.667
When the police
arrested gavin,

11:08.669 --> 11:10.035
I did what
walter would have wanted.

11:10.037 --> 11:11.970
I hired him a lawyer
and paid his bail.

11:11.972 --> 11:13.304
I never thought he'd run.

11:13.306 --> 11:15.740
He took walter's watch,
a necklace from the safe,

11:15.742 --> 11:17.676
And one of the cars
from the garage.

11:17.678 --> 11:19.310
How does a guy facing
a murder charge even get bail?

11:19.312 --> 11:21.379
By being rich and white.

11:21.381 --> 11:23.014
And no one knows
gavin's missing?

11:23.016 --> 11:24.683
They check in
every 48 hours.

11:24.685 --> 11:25.884
He knew that.

11:25.886 --> 11:27.152
He took off right away.

11:27.154 --> 11:28.620
Which means...

11:28.621 --> 11:30.087
Liv has about 28 hours
to find him.

11:30.090 --> 11:31.222
And you just let her
do this --

11:31.224 --> 11:32.724
Go off to find a murderer
by herself.

11:32.726 --> 11:34.059
You don't say no to liv.

11:34.061 --> 11:36.261
And besides,
she took my car keys.

11:36.263 --> 11:38.830
Olivia, are -- are you sure
you're up to this?

11:38.832 --> 11:39.998
I've seen the news.

11:40.000 --> 11:41.733
The news
is just a lot of rumor

11:41.735 --> 11:43.234
And gossip designed
to get ratings.

11:43.236 --> 11:44.936
So, you<i> can</i> do this?

11:44.938 --> 11:46.304
You're sure?

11:46.306 --> 11:48.373
I will personally find
your stepson and make sure

11:48.375 --> 11:50.275
He returns before anyone
knows he's missing.

11:50.277 --> 11:53.344
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

11:53.346 --> 11:54.879
[ door opens ]

11:54.881 --> 11:57.315
[ clears throat ]
senator grant.

11:57.317 --> 11:58.983
Hello.

11:58.985 --> 12:01.019
What can i do
for you, david?

12:01.020 --> 12:03.054
We are looking at how that
footage got leaked to sally,

12:03.056 --> 12:05.056
And as part
of that investigation,

12:05.058 --> 12:06.791
I need
to examine your computers.

12:06.793 --> 12:08.793
So, that's his move --

12:08.795 --> 12:11.362
Send some sort of swat team
over here to embarrass me.

12:11.364 --> 12:13.765
No, it's just me
and a couple people from tech.

12:13.767 --> 12:15.400
We'll do a quick scan,
nothing public.

12:15.402 --> 12:18.169
No one will know.
[ scoffs ]

12:18.171 --> 12:20.739
Fine.

12:20.741 --> 12:23.174
But just so you know,

12:23.176 --> 12:25.043
You're not here
as the attorney general.

12:25.045 --> 12:26.978
He may have told you
to come here

12:26.980 --> 12:29.047
In some sort
of official capacity,

12:29.049 --> 12:32.283
But right now,
you are no better

12:32.285 --> 12:35.987
Than some two-bit
bus-stop divorce attorney.

12:38.225 --> 12:39.290
Do whatever you want
with the computers.

12:39.292 --> 12:40.358
I have nothing to hide.

12:42.829 --> 12:44.829
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

12:44.831 --> 12:46.448
Olivia: Where now?

12:46.449 --> 12:48.066
Huck: We lost the trail.
Gavin's cell signal dropped.

12:48.068 --> 12:49.968
Either it's dead --
-or he ditched it.

12:49.970 --> 12:51.002
Gavin's broke.

12:51.004 --> 12:52.370
His accounts are frozen.

12:52.372 --> 12:55.273
He needs gas, food,
a place to lay his head.

12:55.275 --> 12:56.441
He needs money.

12:56.443 --> 12:58.143
Uh, brock brothers,

12:58.145 --> 13:00.879
A pawn shop about 30 miles
outside of fayetteville.

13:00.881 --> 13:03.481
A pic du midi 1591 watch
just went up on their site.

13:03.483 --> 13:05.817
That's walter's watch.
Text me the address.

13:05.819 --> 13:08.219
I informed him how
there ain't much of a market

13:08.221 --> 13:10.088
Around here
for sissy euro watches.

13:10.090 --> 13:12.040
[ chuckles ]

13:12.041 --> 13:13.991
He took $500 and let me put
the rest on consignment.

13:13.994 --> 13:15.160
Amazing
what folks will do

13:15.162 --> 13:16.995
When their backs
are against the wall.

13:16.997 --> 13:19.497
Do i know you?

13:19.499 --> 13:22.567
No, i don't think so.

13:22.569 --> 13:25.303
If he comes back...

13:25.305 --> 13:26.805
"ruth."

13:26.807 --> 13:28.173
You got it, ruthie.

13:28.175 --> 13:29.274
[ chuckles ]

13:29.276 --> 13:31.142
He sold the watch,
but not for much.

13:31.144 --> 13:32.944
He needs money.
The car's probably next.

13:32.946 --> 13:34.012
Quinn: Well, there are
more used-car lots

13:34.014 --> 13:35.313
In north carolina
than people.

13:35.315 --> 13:37.348
We're running out of time.
-Yeah, no kidding.

13:37.350 --> 13:39.284
Hey, huck's compiling a list
of dealerships in the area.

13:39.286 --> 13:40.251
We'll e-mail them.

13:41.588 --> 13:43.855
-Hold on.
-What?

13:43.857 --> 13:46.858
I don't think
he's at a car lot.

13:46.860 --> 13:48.560
[ coins clinking,
slot machines humming ]

13:57.437 --> 13:59.103
Table's ice-cold.

13:59.105 --> 14:02.273
Hopefully i can
warm it up.

14:04.311 --> 14:06.211
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

14:08.982 --> 14:11.015
Thank you.
I needed that.

14:11.017 --> 14:13.585
[ chuckles ]
[ sighs ]

14:13.587 --> 14:16.855
I don't really have
any interest in paying for sex.

14:16.857 --> 14:20.158
No offense, just...

14:20.160 --> 14:24.229
Let's just take it slow
and see if your luck keeps up.

14:28.101 --> 14:29.100
Oh.

14:29.102 --> 14:30.501
[ chuckles ]
damn.

14:34.107 --> 14:36.241
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

14:36.243 --> 14:39.544
Make a scene, and the feds
will be here in minutes.

14:41.114 --> 14:42.580
There's a lot
of other ways

14:42.582 --> 14:45.216
For a gal
to make some money, gavin.

14:52.959 --> 14:55.126
Gavin: You're not
exactly what i picture

14:55.128 --> 14:57.395
When i picture
bounty hunters.

14:57.397 --> 14:59.230
I'm not
a bounty hunter.

14:59.232 --> 15:01.299
Your stepmother
is worried about you.

15:01.301 --> 15:04.102
[ sighs ] steph's not worried.
She's tying up loose ends.

15:04.104 --> 15:06.905
She's been waiting a long time
for my dad to kick off,

15:06.907 --> 15:10.108
And now that he has,
i'm in her way.

15:12.145 --> 15:13.645
Look,
no offense [sniffs]

15:13.647 --> 15:15.346
But i could
probably take you out.

15:15.348 --> 15:17.982
There's not too many people
i can say that about, but you?

15:17.984 --> 15:19.484
I think
i'd have a good shot.

15:19.486 --> 15:21.953
[ laughs ]
so, what's your plan here?

15:21.955 --> 15:23.955
Keep me cuffed
to this stool

15:23.957 --> 15:26.024
And play blackjack
until i pass out?

15:32.065 --> 15:34.699
My plan just arrived.

15:36.636 --> 15:39.137
Nice to see you.

15:39.139 --> 15:40.705
Figured you might need
some help.

15:40.707 --> 15:42.106
[ chuckles ]

15:42.108 --> 15:43.558
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

15:43.559 --> 15:45.009
Old people slip
and fall every day.

15:45.011 --> 15:46.544
Not right after fighting
with their sons.

15:46.546 --> 15:49.013
-It wasn't right after.
-But you did have a fight.

15:49.015 --> 15:50.682
[ sighs ] there was
this house i was building

15:50.684 --> 15:52.984
In the shenandoah valley,
and he wouldn't give me

15:52.986 --> 15:54.552
The money to finish it
'cause he's lame.

15:54.554 --> 15:56.521
But the yelling --
that wasn't fighting.

15:56.523 --> 15:58.222
That's just how he talked to me.

15:58.224 --> 16:00.058
-I kind of get why.
-No need to be rude.

16:00.060 --> 16:02.126
Anyway, later on,
i heard a noise,

16:02.128 --> 16:04.362
And there he was
at the bottom of the stairs.

16:04.364 --> 16:06.197
Hell,
<i> she</i> could have pushed him.

16:06.199 --> 16:08.166
The whole thing
is just so crazy.

16:08.168 --> 16:10.101
How could anyone think
i killed my father?

16:10.103 --> 16:11.602
What possible motive
could i have?

16:11.604 --> 16:13.571
What possible motive
could your stepmother have?

16:13.573 --> 16:15.473
She's got a great one --
been seeing some guy

16:15.475 --> 16:17.308
On the side
for the past five years.

16:17.310 --> 16:20.111
And she signed
this intense prenup
when she and my dad got hitched.

16:20.113 --> 16:21.612
We did the background
check on her.

16:21.614 --> 16:24.115
Walter was very clear -- if she
cheated, she'd get nothing.

16:24.117 --> 16:26.651
And now,
she gets a billion dollars.

16:26.653 --> 16:28.686
Makes spending 20 years
with a guy who's old enough

16:28.688 --> 16:32.290
To be your dad
look like easy work.

16:32.292 --> 16:34.525
I'm not lying.
Look into it if you want.

16:34.527 --> 16:38.096
Pulled stephanie price's
text logs, and nothing so far.

16:38.098 --> 16:39.263
[ sighs ]
walter's e-mail --

16:39.265 --> 16:41.032
An easy hack,
but nothing there, either.

16:41.034 --> 16:43.568
I also ran the qr14 face rec
on every visitor

16:43.570 --> 16:45.436
In and out of the house
for the past five years,

16:45.438 --> 16:47.338
And apart from the fact
that michael bolton

16:47.340 --> 16:50.341
Performed at walter's birthday
last year, nothing odd.

16:50.343 --> 16:53.544
Danny mendoza,
<i> capital spill.</i>

16:53.546 --> 16:55.513
Any comment on your boss's
extracurricular activities?

16:55.515 --> 16:57.281
-How'd you get in here?
-Just a few questions.

16:57.283 --> 16:59.117
When did you all learn
of the affair?

16:59.119 --> 17:00.585
-Give me the camera.
-It's private property.

17:00.587 --> 17:02.653
-Give me the camera.
-Really? No comment?

17:02.655 --> 17:05.423
Did your boss ever say what
the president was like in bed?

17:05.425 --> 17:07.525
[ both grunting ]

17:08.762 --> 17:11.162
You can't take that.

17:11.164 --> 17:12.397
You are trespassing.

17:12.399 --> 17:13.882
There is not a scratch
on you.

17:13.883 --> 17:15.366
There is no video
to prove i took your video.

17:15.368 --> 17:17.135
If you don't get out of here,
i will kick your ass,

17:17.137 --> 17:18.669
And you can tell everyone
a girl beat you up.

17:18.671 --> 17:20.471
Or i can give you to him,

17:20.473 --> 17:23.374
And you won't be able to tell
anyone anything ever again.

17:23.376 --> 17:25.076
Your choice.

17:25.078 --> 17:26.544
[ groans ]

17:26.546 --> 17:28.446
[ breathing heavily ]

17:28.448 --> 17:32.350
[ footsteps departing ]

17:32.352 --> 17:34.352
[ breathing heavily ]

17:34.354 --> 17:36.721
[ door closes ]

17:36.723 --> 17:40.425
"fixed," huh?

17:40.427 --> 17:42.693
[ door closes ]

17:42.695 --> 17:44.162
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

17:44.164 --> 17:46.264
[ indistinct shouting ]

17:46.266 --> 17:47.765
If there were something to say,

17:47.767 --> 17:50.301
I'd be saying it,
but there isn't, so i'm not.

17:50.303 --> 17:52.203
Are the photos real?
I have nothing
to say at this time.

17:52.205 --> 17:54.172
Is the president having
an affair with olivia pope?

17:54.174 --> 17:56.107
Are there any other topics
you'd like to cover?

17:56.109 --> 17:58.209
[ indistinct shouting ]
ashley?

17:58.211 --> 17:59.711
<i> Are you not answering</i>
<i> these questions</i>

17:59.712 --> 18:01.212
<i> Because you're afraid</i>
<i> to be caught in a lie?</i>

18:01.213 --> 18:02.713
Tricky, tricky.
<i> I'm not answering</i>
<i> these questions</i>

18:02.714 --> 18:04.214
<i> Because there is nothing</i>
<i> to say at this time.</i>

18:04.217 --> 18:06.717
That's all for now.
Thak you, everyone.

18:06.719 --> 18:08.619
[ indistinct shouting ]

18:08.621 --> 18:11.856
[ chuckles ] they ain't buyin'
what you're sellin', girlfriend.

18:11.858 --> 18:13.658
[ door closes ]
[ exhaling sharply ]

18:13.660 --> 18:16.461
[ cellphone ringing ]

18:16.463 --> 18:18.629
I know i'm supposed
to be sensitive

18:18.631 --> 18:21.265
To your plight or whatever,
but if you're calling to gloat.

18:21.267 --> 18:23.201
Cyrus: [ laughing ] funny.
Funny stuff, red.

18:23.203 --> 18:25.436
You practically wrote
kimmel's monologue for him.

18:25.438 --> 18:26.838
Joke, joke, joke.

18:26.840 --> 18:28.706
Goodbye, cyrus.

18:28.708 --> 18:30.842
-You want some advice?
-What? No.

18:30.844 --> 18:32.510
Yes.

18:32.512 --> 18:34.445
-Be the adult.
-Be the adult?

18:34.447 --> 18:36.314
Bring mellie back
to the white house.
She came back.

18:36.316 --> 18:38.382
He threw her out.
He wants nothing to do with her.

18:38.384 --> 18:39.884
Listen
to me say it again --

18:39.886 --> 18:42.386
Be the adult.

18:42.388 --> 18:44.522
Be the adult and...?

18:44.524 --> 18:46.757
Be the adult.

18:46.759 --> 18:48.860
Damn it, are you drunk?
Are you day-drinking?

18:48.862 --> 18:50.862
Because i need
some serious help here.

18:50.864 --> 18:53.431
Red...

18:53.433 --> 18:55.500
How does leadership come?
Is it given to you? No.

18:55.502 --> 18:57.335
You want to lead,
be the leader.

18:57.337 --> 19:00.238
Everyone else will automatically
become the follower.

19:00.240 --> 19:03.808
You want potus to fall in line,
to behave.

19:03.810 --> 19:05.610
Be the adult.
He'll become the child.

19:05.612 --> 19:07.545
That's the secret
of the oval office, red.

19:07.547 --> 19:10.181
You want the power?
You want to be the kingmaker?

19:10.183 --> 19:11.782
You want to be the hand
that rules?

19:11.784 --> 19:13.384
You are the adult.

19:13.386 --> 19:14.652
He is the child,

19:14.654 --> 19:16.587
And you don't ask children
when bedtime is,

19:16.589 --> 19:18.623
And you don't listen
to children when they say

19:18.625 --> 19:20.391
They don't want
their vegetables.

19:20.393 --> 19:22.894
You threaten them and you
make them eat those vegetables.

19:22.896 --> 19:24.795
You're
a terrible father.

19:24.797 --> 19:25.663
Whatever.

19:25.665 --> 19:28.566
You stand at that podium

19:28.568 --> 19:30.601
In front of the white house
press corps and be the adult.

19:30.603 --> 19:32.570
You bring mellie back
to the white house.

19:32.572 --> 19:33.804
Be the adult.

19:33.806 --> 19:35.573
You're trying
to get me fired.

19:35.575 --> 19:37.842
He'll fire you maybe,
but only for a few hours.

19:37.844 --> 19:40.344
All children eventually do
as they're told.

19:40.346 --> 19:41.279
Be the adult.

19:44.517 --> 19:45.616
Thanks, quinn.

19:45.618 --> 19:47.285
His story checks out.

19:47.287 --> 19:48.920
Stephanie is sleeping
with a restaurant owner

19:48.922 --> 19:50.721
Named romeo sarconi --
has been for years.
[ toilet flushing ]

19:50.723 --> 19:52.557
And you may be right that
your father found out
about the affair.

19:52.559 --> 19:54.392
He made an appointment
with his lawyer

19:54.394 --> 19:55.793
To change his will
the day before he died.

19:55.795 --> 19:56.794
I told you.

19:56.796 --> 19:58.629
Now, i am starving.

19:58.631 --> 20:00.498
Can we get some food?
-What did i say?

20:00.500 --> 20:02.567
-Stop whining?
-Stop whining.

20:02.569 --> 20:05.203
Fine, i'm grateful

20:05.205 --> 20:07.305
To be trapped
in a cheap motel room

20:07.306 --> 20:09.406
That smells like urine
and insecticide with you two,

20:09.409 --> 20:11.943
While i starve, headed back
to face a murder charge

20:11.945 --> 20:13.611
For a crime
i did not commit.

20:13.613 --> 20:16.280
I am #blessed.

20:18.251 --> 20:20.685
-What now?
-We investigate further.

20:20.687 --> 20:23.521
We look into stephanie,
dig into her romeo,

20:23.523 --> 20:25.389
See if we can find any evidence
that gavin is innocent.

20:25.391 --> 20:27.358
I'm asking about you.
I could care less about gavin.

20:27.360 --> 20:29.327
Gavin heard that.

20:31.864 --> 20:34.365
Look, at some point,

20:34.367 --> 20:36.968
You're gonna have to leave
this place, face the music.

20:36.970 --> 20:39.804
You wanted
to be with him.

20:39.806 --> 20:42.740
You wanted to be with him
so much that i --

20:42.742 --> 20:44.642
What's changed?

20:44.644 --> 20:48.379
-What's changed?
-Um, wait a minute.

20:48.381 --> 20:50.514
Hold on, you're on tv.
<i> Ms. Pope hasn't been seen</i>
<i> since this news broke,</i>

20:50.516 --> 20:52.483
<i> Leading to rampant speculation</i>
<i> as to her whereabouts.</i>

20:52.485 --> 20:53.851
<i> Her involvement</i>
<i> with the president</i>

20:53.853 --> 20:55.586
<i> Still yet to be confirmed --</i>

20:55.588 --> 20:56.954
Wait, you're the --

20:56.956 --> 21:00.491
I'm not the only one
on the run, huh?

21:00.493 --> 21:01.726
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

21:01.728 --> 21:03.261
What is taking so long?

21:03.263 --> 21:05.329
It's a private law firm,
not the pentagon.

21:05.331 --> 21:07.898
I've already bypassed the main
grid of their security program,

21:07.900 --> 21:11.035
And i'm accessing all files
linked to walter price.

21:11.037 --> 21:12.403
Five seconds to go.

21:12.405 --> 21:14.505
There.
-What do you got?

21:14.507 --> 21:16.307
Purchase agreements,
uh,

21:16.309 --> 21:19.377
Retail leases, ground leases,
industrial leases.

21:19.379 --> 21:21.612
This guy owned property
all over the globe.

21:21.614 --> 21:23.681
His will, huck!

21:23.683 --> 21:26.517
That's what we're interested in,
not his real estate.

21:26.519 --> 21:28.519
[ scoffs ]

21:28.521 --> 21:30.521
[ sighs ]

21:30.523 --> 21:33.691
[ breathes slowly ]

21:33.693 --> 21:37.495
Oh, is that some kind of coping
mechanism jake taught you?

21:37.497 --> 21:39.530
You feel yourself
getting angry,

21:39.532 --> 21:42.300
So you take a deep breath
and swallow your rage

21:42.302 --> 21:44.035
And everything's fine
'cause you're fixed?

21:44.037 --> 21:45.854
Is that it?

21:45.855 --> 21:47.672
I mean, what does that
even mean, huck --

21:47.674 --> 21:48.973
"fixed"?

21:48.975 --> 21:50.608
Did jake fill you
with beta blockers?

21:50.610 --> 21:51.842
Did he pry
your eyes open

21:51.844 --> 21:53.611
And force you to watch
all kinds of crap?

21:53.613 --> 21:55.479
Did he go all
"clockwork orange" on you?

21:55.481 --> 21:58.382
How the hell
did jake supposedly fix you.

21:58.384 --> 21:59.383
I want to know.

21:59.385 --> 22:01.052
Fine.

22:01.054 --> 22:03.387
You want me gone?
[ thud ]

22:03.389 --> 22:05.456
I'm gone.

22:05.458 --> 22:07.591
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

22:07.593 --> 22:09.727
[ indistinct shouting ]
was olivia pope involved
with the president

22:09.729 --> 22:11.529
At the same time she was
on the government's payroll?

22:11.531 --> 22:13.898
I will not be answering any
questions about olivia pope.

22:13.900 --> 22:16.367
What is the current status
of the president's marriage?

22:16.369 --> 22:17.935
Again, i would like to ask
if there are any questions

22:17.937 --> 22:19.570
That do not pertain
to the president's marriage.

22:19.572 --> 22:21.605
Can you comment
on senator grant's marriage?

22:21.607 --> 22:23.741
That do not pertain
to the institution of marriage.

22:23.743 --> 22:25.376
Can you at least
confirm sightings

22:25.377 --> 22:27.010
Of senator grant
at the white house today?

22:27.013 --> 22:28.612
Is it true
the senator has been living

22:28.614 --> 22:30.014
At blair house
for the past several days?

22:30.016 --> 22:33.351
[ indistinct shouting ]

22:33.353 --> 22:35.820
[ shouting fades, distorts ]

22:41.894 --> 22:43.928
The first lady lives
in the white house,

22:43.930 --> 22:46.030
Like every first lady
since abigail adams.

22:46.032 --> 22:47.765
What the hell is she doing?
<i> Tell us when</i>
<i> we can expect a statement</i>

22:47.767 --> 22:49.900
<i> From the president</i>
<i> and senator grant.</i>

22:49.902 --> 22:52.436
<i> The president and his wife</i>
<i> are handling this</i>

22:52.438 --> 22:54.105
<i> As they should --</i>
<i> privately, as a team.</i>

22:54.107 --> 22:55.940
<i> Therefore, there is</i>
<i> no statement to be made.</i>

22:55.942 --> 22:57.775
She's making
a statement.

22:57.777 --> 23:00.077
Fix it.

23:04.150 --> 23:05.883
The statement
that the nation's first lady,

23:05.885 --> 23:07.084
Senator mellie grant,

23:07.086 --> 23:09.553
Is indeed still living
at the white house

23:09.555 --> 23:12.556
Came from press secretary
abigail whelan just moments ago.

23:12.558 --> 23:14.091
The press
has received a statement

23:14.093 --> 23:15.926
That both the president
and his wife are still --

23:15.928 --> 23:17.528
And i quote -- "a team."

23:17.530 --> 23:19.163
How you can
possibly not understand this

23:19.165 --> 23:20.898
As a direct statement
from the white house

23:20.900 --> 23:22.466
To the american public
on the strength

23:22.468 --> 23:23.768
Of the first couple's
marriage

23:23.770 --> 23:25.669
Is beyond my ability
to comprehend.

23:25.671 --> 23:27.471
Elizabeth:
You don't set strategy.

23:27.473 --> 23:29.006
<i> I</i> set strategy.

23:29.008 --> 23:31.575
The president
sets strategy.

23:31.577 --> 23:34.145
You are a mouthpiece
for the administration,

23:34.147 --> 23:36.046
Nothing more.
I was only trying
to right the ship.

23:36.048 --> 23:37.681
I don't care
what you were trying.

23:37.683 --> 23:39.550
The only reason
you're not out on your ass,

23:39.552 --> 23:41.118
Trolling k street,
knocking on the doors

23:41.120 --> 23:42.686
Of every third-rate
p.R. Firm

23:42.688 --> 23:44.188
Desperate enough
to hire you right now

23:44.190 --> 23:47.191
Is that firing you would
only add fuel to this scandal.

23:47.193 --> 23:49.960
Consider yourself lucky.

23:52.899 --> 23:54.698
[ gavin sniffs ]

23:54.700 --> 23:56.567
I appreciate you bringing me
here. I really was starving.

23:56.569 --> 23:59.103
Parenting 101 --
reward complaining.

23:59.105 --> 24:00.971
[ clears throat ]

24:00.973 --> 24:02.606
Ahh.

24:02.608 --> 24:03.808
Where you going?

24:03.810 --> 24:05.075
Relax.

24:05.077 --> 24:06.644
Going to the bathroom.

24:10.750 --> 24:12.716
I should go make sure
he doesn't get beat up.

24:12.718 --> 24:14.919
[ sighs ]

24:14.921 --> 24:16.620
[ indistinct conversations ]

24:20.460 --> 24:22.159
[ cellphone ringing ]

24:24.063 --> 24:25.896
Yeah?

24:25.898 --> 24:27.665
-We were wrong.
-What?

24:27.667 --> 24:29.967
Walter was going to change
his will, but it was gavin

24:29.969 --> 24:31.769
He was cutting out of it,
not his stepmother.

24:31.771 --> 24:33.037
Are you sure?

24:33.039 --> 24:34.572
Yeah, the law firm
they were using --

24:34.574 --> 24:35.940
We hacked
their in-house network.

24:35.942 --> 24:38.075
I saw the will,
and there's more.

24:38.077 --> 24:40.144
Turns out gavin was forging
checks in his dad's name

24:40.146 --> 24:41.812
For some house
he was building.

24:41.814 --> 24:43.814
And his father
found out about it?
Yup.

24:43.816 --> 24:46.584
In fact, he was about to go
to the police, but then he died.

24:46.586 --> 24:48.018
Are you olivia pope?

24:48.020 --> 24:49.537
Um...

24:49.538 --> 24:51.055
Oh, my god,
the little guy was right.

24:51.057 --> 24:52.756
It is her.
Here, take a picture.
Um...

24:52.758 --> 24:54.825
-Okay, no, i --
-just a quick one. Really.

24:54.827 --> 24:55.926
No. Thank you.
Okay.

24:55.928 --> 24:57.728
Okay, thank -- thank you.

24:57.730 --> 24:58.796
-Thank you so much.
-It's olivia pope.

24:58.798 --> 25:00.231
-It's olivia pope.
-It's olivia...

25:00.233 --> 25:02.132
-Can i have my picture taken --
-no, ma'am.

25:02.134 --> 25:04.535
You slept with the president!
[ laughs ]

25:04.537 --> 25:05.870
Okay, excuse me.
[ indistinct shouting ]

25:05.872 --> 25:07.171
Oh, my god,
i want a picture.

25:07.173 --> 25:10.207
All right, move. Move.
Move. Liv? Out of the way.

25:10.209 --> 25:12.076
Out of the way.
Come on. Come on.
[ indistinct conversations ]

25:12.078 --> 25:13.511
Liv, come on.

25:13.513 --> 25:15.546
Woman: Excuse me.
Excuse me. Come on.

25:15.548 --> 25:18.516
Put your head down.
Everybody, move. People.

25:22.021 --> 25:23.821
-He's furious.
-He's not furious.

25:23.823 --> 25:25.289
Oh, he's furious
with me.

25:25.291 --> 25:27.224
He's not furious with you.
He's frustrated with himself.

25:27.226 --> 25:28.609
Remember -- he's a baby.

25:28.610 --> 25:29.993
What do babies do when
they get frustrated?

25:29.996 --> 25:32.029
Do i have a baby,
cyrus?

25:32.031 --> 25:33.297
Has anyone come out
of me?

25:33.299 --> 25:34.665
Usually they scream,

25:34.666 --> 25:36.032
Scream their little heads off --
"wah, wah."

25:36.035 --> 25:37.167
Shut up and speak.

25:37.169 --> 25:39.036
You're playing this
perfectly, red.

25:39.038 --> 25:40.804
That briefing today
was magic.

25:40.806 --> 25:42.873
He doesn't know it.
He can't appreciate it.

25:42.875 --> 25:45.209
But you may have single-handedly
saved his presidency.

25:45.211 --> 25:47.878
He doesn't care about
his presidency, cyrus.

25:47.880 --> 25:49.079
He only cares about liv.

25:49.081 --> 25:50.047
What does liv want him
to say?

25:50.049 --> 25:51.215
What does liv want him
to do?

25:51.217 --> 25:53.017
Yeah, what does liv
want him to do?

25:53.019 --> 25:54.652
I don't know. She's gone.
She ran away.

25:54.654 --> 25:56.587
-Then you do know.
-I don't!

25:56.589 --> 25:58.956
Stop telling me the opposite
of what i am telling you.

25:58.958 --> 26:01.025
I am too tired for this!
I don't!

26:01.027 --> 26:03.327
You do -- nobody knows
olivia pope better than you do.

26:03.329 --> 26:05.129
The president
of the united states

26:05.131 --> 26:07.831
Needs you to tell him what she
wants him to do, and you know.

26:07.833 --> 26:11.268
So, be the adult here
and tell him.

26:11.270 --> 26:12.937
Why are you doing this?

26:12.939 --> 26:14.939
You're gone.
Why do you care?
Red.

26:14.941 --> 26:17.074
Who do i hate
more than elizabeth north?

26:17.076 --> 26:18.943
No one?

26:18.945 --> 26:20.644
And who does
elizabeth north hate

26:20.646 --> 26:21.745
Even more
than she hates me?

26:21.747 --> 26:23.814
-Mellie.
-Right.

26:29.255 --> 26:31.789
[ knock on door ]

26:31.791 --> 26:33.624
You wanted to see me,
mr. President?

26:33.626 --> 26:35.092
Susan, i need you
to fill in for me

26:35.094 --> 26:36.660
At this business roundtable
in the morning.

26:36.662 --> 26:39.129
Oh, sir, i'm talking

26:39.131 --> 26:41.665
To 1,200 high-school students
tomorrow morning.

26:41.667 --> 26:43.801
-We're talking college access.
-You'll have to reschedule.

26:43.803 --> 26:45.869
But i have it all set up.

26:45.871 --> 26:47.171
Everyone's filling out
financial-aid forms together --

26:47.173 --> 26:50.007
I don't have time
to argue with you.

26:50.009 --> 26:51.609
We done?

26:51.611 --> 26:54.078
Yes, sir.

26:59.285 --> 27:00.751
No, sir.

27:00.753 --> 27:04.154
I'm wondering...

27:04.156 --> 27:06.790
Do you think about us?

27:06.792 --> 27:07.858
What?

27:07.860 --> 27:10.127
Do you think about us --

27:10.129 --> 27:12.763
The people who voted
for you, america?

27:12.765 --> 27:14.231
Do you think about us
when you're having

27:14.233 --> 27:17.101
An affair
in the white house --

27:17.103 --> 27:18.636
In our house?

27:18.638 --> 27:21.872
Do you think about why
we voted for you?

27:26.012 --> 27:27.911
I fell in love.

27:29.982 --> 27:32.816
Susan,
i'm a flawed person,

27:32.818 --> 27:34.685
Just like anyone else.

27:36.389 --> 27:38.689
Mr. President,

27:38.691 --> 27:41.859
You don't get to be
just like anyone else.

27:41.861 --> 27:44.962
That's not the job
you signed up for.

27:52.004 --> 27:55.105
[ door opens and closes ]

27:56.075 --> 27:57.975
[ sighs ]

28:00.680 --> 28:03.113
Fitz: You can't fix the fact
that i love you.

28:03.115 --> 28:05.082
Sit with me
and watch me choose you.

28:05.084 --> 28:06.984
Rowan:<i> First lady!</i>

28:06.986 --> 28:08.419
<i> Do you have to be</i>
<i> so mediocre?</i>

28:08.421 --> 28:10.821
Jake:<i> I am i love with you,</i>
<i> but you...</i>

28:10.823 --> 28:12.890
<i> Are in love with him.</i>

28:12.892 --> 28:14.158
Fitz:
<i> I don't want to wait.</i>

28:14.160 --> 28:16.326
<i> We put this out</i>
<i> into the light.</i>

28:24.770 --> 28:26.270
[ door opens ]

28:26.272 --> 28:28.205
Jake: Hey.

28:28.207 --> 28:30.240
Hey.

28:30.242 --> 28:32.342
They did not have wine.

28:32.344 --> 28:35.245
Not what your upbringing
would ever call wine, anyway.

28:35.247 --> 28:37.381
Where i'm from,
stuff costs five bucks.

28:37.383 --> 28:39.750
[ keys clatter ]
that's really fancy wine.

28:39.752 --> 28:42.786
Anyway,
i compromised -- beer.

28:42.788 --> 28:44.054
That is not a compromise.
[ chuckles ]

28:44.056 --> 28:45.289
I was hoping
you wouldn't notice.

28:47.760 --> 28:50.494
How bad is it?

28:50.496 --> 28:52.162
Well, the photos
of you from the diner

28:52.164 --> 28:54.231
Are pretty much
everywhere.

28:54.233 --> 28:55.866
The press is swarming.

28:55.868 --> 28:58.969
I passed five, six news vans
driving in circles out there.

28:58.971 --> 29:00.804
They're on the hunt.

29:00.806 --> 29:02.106
But there is good news.

29:03.509 --> 29:05.242
World peace?

29:05.244 --> 29:07.177
The end of poverty?

29:07.179 --> 29:10.447
Women and girls the world over
get to go to school?

29:10.449 --> 29:13.784
A car was reported stolen
from the diner's parking lot --

29:13.786 --> 29:15.519
Red, two-door,
south carolina plates.

29:15.521 --> 29:16.954
Quinn's tracking it now.

29:16.956 --> 29:18.489
She'll call
when she gets a hit.

29:18.491 --> 29:20.190
All we have to do
is wait.

29:20.192 --> 29:22.426
We'll be out
of here soon.

29:24.864 --> 29:26.130
Great.

29:31.237 --> 29:33.437
[ breathes deeply ]

29:33.439 --> 29:35.072
[ sighs ]

29:38.344 --> 29:40.444
[ groans ]

29:43.315 --> 29:45.215
[ sighs ]

29:54.026 --> 29:59.129
I keep asking myself,
"well, when did it happen?

29:59.131 --> 30:02.499
When did i turn right
instead of left?

30:02.501 --> 30:07.204
What choice was it
that decided?

30:07.206 --> 30:12.810
When exactly did i do the thing,
the -- the one step?

30:12.812 --> 30:15.979
What flap
of the butterfly's wings

30:15.981 --> 30:17.915
Brought me to this moment?

30:17.917 --> 30:20.417
How did i get here?"

30:20.419 --> 30:24.087
Because i can't seem
to retrace my steps.

30:24.089 --> 30:25.389
Liv...

30:25.391 --> 30:27.391
I'm scared.

30:27.393 --> 30:29.593
I know.

30:29.595 --> 30:32.062
That's a good thing.

30:36.202 --> 30:39.369
I'm scared,
and i don't know what to do.

30:39.371 --> 30:40.971
I don't have any answers.

30:40.973 --> 30:42.372
How is that a good thing?

30:42.374 --> 30:43.941
[ sighs ]

30:43.943 --> 30:46.143
Well, we're at our best
when we're scared.

30:46.145 --> 30:47.444
Your instincts
are heightened.

30:47.446 --> 30:49.213
Your adrenaline's
right beneath the surface.

30:49.215 --> 30:51.882
Everything's crystal clear

30:51.884 --> 30:55.219
And your focus
becomes like a laser

30:55.221 --> 30:58.455
And you just know
what comes next.

30:58.457 --> 31:01.058
You know what to do.

31:01.060 --> 31:04.328
You know the answers.

31:04.330 --> 31:07.231
And you just act.

31:09.501 --> 31:13.370
Did my father
teach you that?

31:13.372 --> 31:15.439
You really want
to know?

31:26.051 --> 31:27.951
Can we...

31:31.957 --> 31:35.125
Would you mind if...

31:35.127 --> 31:37.895
No.

31:40.266 --> 31:43.267
No, come on.

31:43.269 --> 31:45.068
Come on.

31:45.070 --> 31:46.970
[ exhales sharply ]

31:59.485 --> 32:03.120
[ sighs ]

32:03.122 --> 32:07.391
I've spent so much time --
years --

32:07.393 --> 32:11.328
Ashamed, with the shame

32:11.330 --> 32:14.998
Pressing on me,
suffocating me.

32:15.000 --> 32:18.101
And for just a little bit,
i let myself breathe,

32:18.103 --> 32:23.206
And...Then those photos
come out.

32:23.208 --> 32:25.108
And...

32:29.081 --> 32:32.416
That's what
i'm running from...

32:32.418 --> 32:37.087
That feeling...

32:37.089 --> 32:39.556
The shame.

32:39.558 --> 32:41.658
[ sighs ]

32:45.097 --> 32:47.564
Liv, loving the president
isn't a crime.

32:47.566 --> 32:49.700
[ chuckles, sniffles ]

32:49.702 --> 32:53.136
And yet here i am being
hunted and chased

32:53.138 --> 32:55.505
Like a thief
in the night.

32:55.507 --> 32:58.976
[ chuckles ]

32:58.978 --> 33:02.412
Let's face it --
i'm basically gavin.

33:14.560 --> 33:16.660
[ footsteps approaching ]

33:20.399 --> 33:22.399
Mr. President?

33:27.473 --> 33:30.273
Speak.

33:30.275 --> 33:33.310
I assume you heard
what happened with olivia

33:33.312 --> 33:36.046
In that diner
and that you saw those photos?

33:36.048 --> 33:37.247
The world
saw those photos.

33:37.249 --> 33:39.082
So then you know
who she's with.

33:41.653 --> 33:43.053
What's your point?

33:45.557 --> 33:50.427
My point is that olivia's doing
what olivia always does, sir.

33:50.429 --> 33:52.062
She's trying to stay out
of the storm.

33:52.064 --> 33:53.463
It hasn't even
really begun yet.

33:53.465 --> 33:55.232
The category 5
that's been building,

33:55.234 --> 33:57.634
Picking up strength ever since
sally released those photos --

33:57.636 --> 33:59.436
Right now, it's still somewhere
out in the middle of the ocean.

33:59.438 --> 34:00.704
But the moment
liv stops running,

34:00.706 --> 34:02.339
The moment she stops hiding
and steps back

34:02.341 --> 34:06.043
In that spotlight --
that cyclone makes landfall.

34:06.045 --> 34:08.345
And everything in her world
gets violently swept away.

34:08.347 --> 34:09.513
That kind of pressure,
that kind of scrutiny --

34:09.515 --> 34:11.048
It would be unbearable.

34:11.050 --> 34:12.416
Who would want to live
through that?

34:12.418 --> 34:14.284
What kind of woman would choose
to live through that?

34:14.286 --> 34:16.286
Olivia pope
is never gonna tell you

34:16.288 --> 34:18.488
She's okay with that kind
of life, mr. President,

34:18.490 --> 34:20.724
No matter
how many times you ask.

34:20.726 --> 34:22.826
[ exhales sharply ]

34:26.131 --> 34:28.265
David: Mr. President, i have
the results of our inquiry.

34:28.267 --> 34:31.334
Our fbi cyber-security team
was able to confirm

34:31.336 --> 34:33.804
That the leak did originate
from a computer

34:33.806 --> 34:36.740
Connected to the first lady's
private, interoffice network.

34:36.742 --> 34:38.275
We've combed
through her digital files --

34:38.277 --> 34:40.410
It doesn't matter.
Thank you, david.

34:41.413 --> 34:43.313
[ telephone ringing ]

34:48.287 --> 34:49.519
What?

34:49.521 --> 34:53.824
I apologize.

34:53.826 --> 34:56.359
Come home.

34:56.361 --> 34:58.095
[ sighs ]

34:58.097 --> 35:01.598
[ cellphone ringing ]

35:01.600 --> 35:03.767
Mm.

35:03.769 --> 35:07.404
[ groans ]
[ exhales sharply ]

35:07.406 --> 35:09.473
Quinn,
did you find the car?

35:09.475 --> 35:11.274
Yeah, gavin abandoned it
a couple miles

35:11.276 --> 35:12.676
From some lake
in the middle of nowhere.

35:12.678 --> 35:13.961
Look, i'm sorry, liv.

35:13.962 --> 35:15.245
The cops say
there's no sign of him.

35:15.247 --> 35:16.480
You know
where that lake is?

35:16.482 --> 35:18.215
Looks like
outside linville, virginia.

35:18.217 --> 35:20.250
-That's the shenandoah valley.
-We know where he is.

35:20.252 --> 35:22.085
Gavin?

35:25.390 --> 35:26.790
Still cold.

35:26.792 --> 35:29.392
Come on, gavin.

35:29.394 --> 35:31.595
We know you're in here.
-Get out of my house!

35:31.597 --> 35:33.830
Jake: A nail gun?
Really?

35:33.832 --> 35:35.398
Put that thing down.

35:35.400 --> 35:37.667
Make me.

35:37.669 --> 35:40.837
Fine, if you really want
to play that way.

35:40.839 --> 35:42.572
[ nail gun fires ]
aah!

35:42.574 --> 35:43.673
-Sorry.
-Are you kidding me?

35:43.675 --> 35:45.842
Sorry.

35:50.549 --> 35:52.849
I'm busy, david.

35:52.851 --> 35:53.817
David:
I'm sure you are.

35:53.819 --> 35:55.218
So, was i, reading through

35:55.220 --> 35:57.454
All the first lady's
e-mail correspondence

35:57.456 --> 35:59.556
Like some bizarrely overpaid
first-year associate.

35:59.558 --> 36:01.424
This is the report

36:01.426 --> 36:03.326
From the justice department's
investigation.

36:03.328 --> 36:04.728
The president says
he doesn't want it,

36:04.730 --> 36:06.663
So, i'm giving it to you.
-What's it say?

36:06.665 --> 36:08.398
What i wrote is that,
while mellie's key code

36:08.400 --> 36:10.934
Was used to take the security
footage from the server,

36:10.936 --> 36:13.303
There's no evidence
of a download on her computer.

36:13.305 --> 36:14.905
So, officially,

36:14.907 --> 36:17.908
The investigation's
inconclusive.

36:17.910 --> 36:19.643
What i read,
on the other hand...

36:19.645 --> 36:20.610
In mellie's e-mail?

36:20.612 --> 36:22.746
Tell me.

36:22.748 --> 36:24.748
Wait, no.
You probably shouldn't.

36:24.750 --> 36:26.917
You know, i never
really figured the concept

36:26.919 --> 36:28.785
Of plausible deniability
would feature

36:28.787 --> 36:30.720
Quite so prominently
in my adult life.

36:30.722 --> 36:32.322
[ chuckles ]
me neither.

36:32.324 --> 36:33.823
I really do feel like
a divorce lawyer.

36:33.825 --> 36:35.926
Anyway, i guess it's nothing
a little bourbon won't fix.

36:35.928 --> 36:38.361
-See you.
-See you.

36:42.467 --> 36:44.935
[ cheryl lynn's "got to be real"
plays ]

36:53.212 --> 36:56.580
Sir, charlotte
just told me the map room

36:56.582 --> 36:58.648
Is being set up
for a sit-down with noah baker.

36:58.650 --> 37:00.951
What's going on?
-Hello, elizabeth.

37:00.953 --> 37:02.819
Fitz: Mellie and i are doing
an interview with noah.

37:02.821 --> 37:04.788
Someone
should have told you.

37:04.790 --> 37:06.756
Yes, they should have.

37:06.758 --> 37:08.358
Sorry about that, liz.

37:08.360 --> 37:10.493
 to be real 

37:10.495 --> 37:11.861
[ indistinct conversations ]

37:11.863 --> 37:13.830
Well, i see you got
what you wanted.

37:13.832 --> 37:15.799
The first lady is back
in the white house.

37:15.801 --> 37:17.534
-She is?
-Don't play dumb.

37:17.536 --> 37:19.703
They're doing an interview
with noah baker.

37:19.705 --> 37:21.638
This is the final nail
in your coffin.

37:21.640 --> 37:24.708
Pack your things and then get
the hell out of here.

37:24.710 --> 37:27.377
I don't think so.

37:27.379 --> 37:29.246
Excuse me?

37:29.248 --> 37:31.514
You leaked those photos
of olivia and the president.

37:31.516 --> 37:32.682
-Don't be ridiculous.
-Why'd you do it?

37:32.684 --> 37:34.384
You wanted to get rid
of olivia pope?

37:34.386 --> 37:36.253
I have no idea
what you're --
you used to work for mellie.

37:36.255 --> 37:38.388
You knew her key code.
You had access.

37:38.390 --> 37:40.857
You leaked those photos
to sally langston.

37:40.859 --> 37:44.694
 our love is here to stay 

37:44.696 --> 37:45.862
 what you think 

37:45.864 --> 37:48.265
[ sighs ]

37:48.267 --> 37:49.899
Who have you told?
The president?

37:49.901 --> 37:52.802
I haven't told anyone...
Yet.

37:52.804 --> 37:54.804
What do you want?
What's your move?

37:54.806 --> 37:57.307
Am i your bitch now?
You want my job? What?

37:57.309 --> 37:59.309
What i want is
to no longer work for you.

37:59.311 --> 38:00.677
What?

38:00.678 --> 38:02.044
I don't want to work for you.
I want to work with you.

38:02.047 --> 38:03.780
I want us to be a team.
From now on, we're equals.

38:03.782 --> 38:06.750
-Equals?
-Yes.

38:06.752 --> 38:08.551
That's it?

38:08.553 --> 38:09.886
That's --

38:09.888 --> 38:11.955
That's all you want -- equality?
-Equality.

38:11.957 --> 38:13.957
I thought we could both be
the adults around here,

38:13.959 --> 38:15.659
But if you have
a problem with that,

38:15.661 --> 38:17.327
I can certainly try
making you my bitch.

38:17.329 --> 38:19.763
No, no. Equals.

38:19.765 --> 38:22.666
Equals is -- yes.

38:22.668 --> 38:24.934
Good. So, noah baker's
interview questions --

38:24.936 --> 38:26.603
You want
to go over those together?

38:26.605 --> 38:30.473
I'd like that.

38:32.511 --> 38:36.446
